   1:Src/drv8833.c **** /**
   2:Src/drv8833.c ****  * drv8833.c — Differential drive via DRV8833 dual H-bridge
   3:Src/drv8833.c ****  *
   4:Src/drv8833.c ****  * Hardware assignments:
   5:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   Left  motor (Bridge A): AIN1 ← PA6 (TIM3_CH1, AF2)
   6:Src/drv8833.c ****  *                           AIN2 ← PA7 (TIM3_CH2, AF2)
   7:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   Right motor (Bridge B): BIN1 ← PB0 (TIM3_CH3, AF2)
   8:Src/drv8833.c ****  *                           BIN2 ← PB1 (TIM3_CH4, AF2)
   9:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   STBY (nSLEEP)         : PB4  (GPIO output — HIGH = run, LOW = sleep)
  10:Src/drv8833.c ****  *
  11:Src/drv8833.c ****  * TIM3 PWM configuration:
  12:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   Source clock : PCLK1 = 80 MHz
  13:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   Prescaler    : PSC = 3   → timer clock = 80 MHz / 4 = 20 MHz
  14:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   Auto-reload  : ARR = 999 → f_PWM = 20 MHz / 1000 = 20 kHz
  15:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   CCR range    : 0 – 999   → 0 % – 99.9 % duty
  16:Src/drv8833.c ****  *                  CCR = 1000 (> ARR) → 100 % (always HIGH in PWM mode 1)
  17:Src/drv8833.c ****  *
  18:Src/drv8833.c ****  * PWM Mode 1 output (OC1M = 0110):
  19:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   CNT < CCR → output HIGH
  20:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   CNT ≥ CCR → output LOW
  21:Src/drv8833.c ****  *
  22:Src/drv8833.c ****  * Fast-decay speed control:
  23:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   FORWARD  at speed S: CCR_IN1 = S,    CCR_IN2 = 0
  24:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   BACKWARD at speed S: CCR_IN1 = 0,    CCR_IN2 = S
  25:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   BRAKE              : CCR_IN1 = 1000, CCR_IN2 = 1000 → both always HIGH
  26:Src/drv8833.c ****  *                        → DRV8833 xIN1=H xIN2=H → both OUT LOW (slow decay)
  27:Src/drv8833.c ****  *   COAST              : CCR_IN1 = 0,    CCR_IN2 = 0    → both always LOW
  28:Src/drv8833.c ****  *                        → DRV8833 xIN1=L xIN2=L → both OUT Hi-Z (freewheel)
  29:Src/drv8833.c ****  *
  30:Src/drv8833.c ****  * STBY wake-up: datasheet specifies tWAKE ≤ 1 ms (nSLEEP inactive-high to
ARM GAS  C:\Users\Taylor\AppData\Local\Temp\cclYYvkb.s 			page 2


  31:Src/drv8833.c ****  * H-bridge on), so DRV8833_Wake() issues a 1 ms delay after asserting PB4.
  32:Src/drv8833.c ****  *
  33:Src/drv8833.c ****  * NOTE: This file uses TIM3 channels 1–4 and conflicts with motor.c
  34:Src/drv8833.c ****  * (SN754410).  Link only one motor driver at a time — swap motor.c ↔
  35:Src/drv8833.c ****  * drv8833.c in the Makefile C_SOURCES list.
  36:Src/drv8833.c ****  */
  37:Src/drv8833.c **** 
